derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from Latin oblongus 'longish'

entry.def: An oblong is a shape which has two long sides and two short sides and in which all the angles are right angles.

means.word_mean: 1. a plane figure that deviates from a square or circle due to elongation
1. of a leaf shape; having a somewhat elongated form with approximately parallel sides
2. deviating from a square or circle or sphere by being elongated in one direction
